message.content:
cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the satisfiability problem for branching-time temporal logics and presents a game-theoretic framework for it.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the satisfiability problem for temporal logics has important applications in program specification and verification, which are relevant to AI.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses decision procedures for temporal logics using tree automata, tableaux, and axiom systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper analyzes the computational complexity of the satisfiability problem for branching-time temporal logics and presents algorithms for solving it.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses formal languages of omega-words and the use of deterministic omega-automata for recognizing them.
